cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.CL, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the problem of entity resolution (ER) across multiple online social networks (OSNs). The paper uses machine learning techniques to match user profiles across different OSNs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also deals with information retrieval (IR) and data management (DB) aspects, which makes cs.IR and cs.DB likely sub-categories as well. The paper uses natural language processing (NLP) techniques to extract features from user profiles, which makes cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with privacy and anonymity issues, which makes cs.CY (Computers and Society) a possible sub-category.
